<h2 id="section-top">Audiology services (community)</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=967">Pennine Acute Hospitals NHS Trust</a>
</p>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="service-locations clear">
<div class="panel edit-box">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<p class="address">North Manchester General Hospital<br/>0161 720 2678</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContent11a7e9581f504627a5809c62b43bdee1">
</div>
<p><strong>Audiology &amp; Hearing Aid Department</strong></p>
<p><strong>Why might patients be referred to this department?</strong></p>
<p>The audiology and hearing aid clinic is able to assess and manage patients who are complaining of hearing and/or balance difficulties.  We are able to offer quality care to patient suffering from conditions such as hearing loss, tinnitus and vertigo.</p>
<p><strong>What will happen and who will you meet?</strong></p>
<p>When you attend the department the nature of testing performed will be dictated by your problem.  It might be a simple ear examination or a full hearing and balance work up.  Any procedure you are asked to undertake will be fully explained beforehand and verbal consent will be requested.</p>
<p>Depending on your problem and diagnosis you will be assessed and treated by an appropriate member of the audiology team.  We have a large number of qualified members of staff specialising in the diagnosis and management of hearing loss, tinnitus and/or balance disorders.  We are part of a multidisciplinary team with access to ENT medical staff and further complex diagnosis.</p>
<p>If hearing aids are required we offer a range of high quality devices and individual rehabilitation which will be tailored to each patients’ specific needs.  We can maintain your hearing aids regularly and will update and review hearing prescriptions on a regular basis.</p>
<p><strong>Where can you find these services?</strong></p>
<p>The audiology department is based at North Manchester General Hospital in Out Patient B.  We also offer appointments at local health centres.  Please contact the department directly for more information.</p>
<p><strong>When is the department open?</strong></p>
<p>Appointments are available from 8.00 am to 6.00 pm Monday to Friday at North Manchester General Hospital and a number of community clinics. We also provide a service at North Manchester General Hospital only between 9.00 -1.30pm on Saturdays – by appointment only.</p></div>
</div>
